CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 2 reads: "At Mayors' Met, Discuss Urban Renewal - Shown at the Kennedy Conference of Urban Renewal, held Monday at the Hotel Penn-Sheraton and attended by mayors from 55 U.S. cities, were...(right photo, left to right) Richard S. Dowdy, former Pittsburgh Urban League executive, now with the New Haven, Conn., city government; New Haven's Mayor Richard C. Lee, Congressman Powell, Philadelphia's Mayor Richardson Dilworth and New Orleans' Mayor deLesseps Morrison-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Richard S. Dowdy, New Haven Mayor Richard C. Lee, Congressman Adam C. Powell Jr., Philadelphia Mayor Richardson Dilworth, and New Orleans Mayor deLesseps Morrison, standing in Penn - Sheraton Hotel for Kennedy Conference on Urban Renewal
